OL,3,CEx-employee helped himself to #52,000
OL,4,Cworth of fuel on company account
OL,6,FHe was expected to return the cards
OL,7,Fwhen he left the company in August the
OL,8,Fsame year.
OL,10,FBut in November 2019, the company's
OL,11,Fcompliance manager noticed a
OL,12,Fdiscrepancy of #52,310 in the books.
OL,13,FHe reported the matter to Action Fraud
OL,14,Fwhich later handed the case to
OL,15,FLancashire Police.
OL,17,FIt emerged James, of Stanley Road,
OL,18,FNewmarket, had purchased 33,470 litres
OL,19,Fof fuel with the cards in the three
OL,20,Fmonths since he left the company.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
